{
  "texts": [
    "The inadequacy of dictionaries in supporting writing tasks is what led to the development of dedicated writing assistants in the last decade or two (Verlinde and Peeters, 2012, Granger and Paquot, 2015, Tarp et al. 2017, Alonso-Ramos and García Salido, 2019, Frankenberg-Garcia et al. 2019, Tarp, 2023).",
    "An important factor to consider is the high cognitive demand that the writing process puts on the writer (especially so in their additional language).",
    "Therefore, effective tools for writing should tie up as little of the writer's attention as possible, rather than distract them from the main task.",
    "This is an aspect in which AI tools might hold much promise.",
    "Writing assistants can support the user in the process of writing as it happens, or they can be used for post-editing manual drafts."
  ]
}